      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "1. Avoid hairstyles that are too trendy or flashy, such as shaved heads, brightly colored hair, or excessively styled hair.\n2. Refrain from wearing hats or caps, as they can be seen as unprofessional.\n3. Avoid overly casual grooming habits, such as unkempt hair, beards that are too long or unshaven beards, or excessive jewelry.\n4. Keep makeup minimal and natural-looking, avoiding bold or dramatic looks.\n5. Stick to classic, conservative grooming choices that exude professionalism, such as neatly trimmed hair, clean-shaven or well-groomed facial hair, and subtle makeup, if any.\n\nRemember, the goal is to present yourself in a way that commands respect and confidence in a professional setting. Avoid anything that may be perceived as too casual, overly trendy, or unprofessional.",
